Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Roma tomato{1}.

Zest and quarter @lime{1} (zest 1 lime; quarter both for 4 servings).

Mince @garlic{2%cloves}.

Drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Trim and roughly chop @scallions{2}.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine scallions, @olive oil{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings), and @Southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4; be sure to measure). Stir in a pinch of garlic and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add more garlic or lime juice if desired.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water (⅓ cup for 4), @Southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon} (1 TBSP for 4; you'll use the rest later), salt, and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; prick all over with a #fork{} or #knife{}. Season with remaining Southwest spice, salt, and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. When cool enough to handle, slice pork crosswise.

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, half the lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and a large pinch of salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), remaining lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper. Divide rice and pork between plates. Top rice with bean mixture and crema. Top pork with chimichurri. Cut any remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side.

> When it comes to pork chops, we're always looking for two things: a deeply-browned crust and juicy, tender meat. This dish delivers both with a bright and tangy scallion chimichurri that perfectly balances the meat's richness.

> This delicious dish all comes together in 30 minutes.